<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="64">
When 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Louzada &amp; Wanderley" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="O. B. C. Ribeiro &amp; C. C. Paula" baseAuthorityYear="2012" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Orthophytum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vidaliorum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Orthophytum vidaliorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ribeiro, OBC" journalOrPublisher="Brittonia" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" pagination="145 - 148" publicationUrl="10.1007/s12228-009-9105-9" refId="B4" refString="Ribeiro, OBC, Paula, CC, 2010. A new species of Orthophytum (Bromeliaceae, Bromelioideae) from Minas Gerais, Brazil. Brittonia 62 (2): 145 - 148, 10.1007/s12228-009-9105-9" title="A new species of Orthophytum (Bromeliaceae, Bromelioideae) from Minas Gerais, Brazil." url="10.1007/s12228-009-9105-9" volume="62" year="2010">Ribeiro and Paula (2010)</bibRefCitation>
discussed its morphological relationship with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Versieux &amp; Leme" authorityYear="2007" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Orthophytum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="itambense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Orthophytum itambense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It was emphasized that these species share similar habitat, plant size, leaves, inflorescence and flower structure. Moreover, they state that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Louzada &amp; Wanderley" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="O. B. C. Ribeiro &amp; C. C. Paula" baseAuthorityYear="2012" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Orthophytum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vidaliorum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Orthophytum vidaliorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also closely related to 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Orthophytum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="supthutii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Orthophytum supthutii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which was recently synonymized under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Louzada &amp; Versieux" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="L. B. Sm." class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Lapanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="duartei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Lapanthus duartei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In the same article the authors also mentioned that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Louzada &amp; Wanderley" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="O. B. C. Ribeiro &amp; C. C. Paula" baseAuthorityYear="2012" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Orthophytum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vidaliorum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Orthophytum vidaliorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could be included in a different and unpublished genus proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Louzada, RB" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" refId="B2" refString="Louzada, RB, 2008. Taxonomia e citogenetica das especies de inflorescencia sessile do genero Orthophytum Beer (Bromeliaceae). Master Thesis, Instituto de Botanica, Brasil." title="Taxonomia e citogenetica das especies de inflorescencia sessile do genero Orthophytum Beer (Bromeliaceae). Master Thesis, Instituto de Botanica, Brasil." year="2008">Louzada (2008)</bibRefCitation>
in his 
<normalizedToken originalValue="master’s">master's</normalizedToken>
thesis, which later was validly published under the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="R.B.Louzada &amp; L.M.Versieux" authorityYear="2010" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Lapanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Lapanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Louzada, RB" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" pagination="497 - 503" publicationUrl="10.1600/036364410792495908" refId="B3" refString="Louzada, RB, Versieux, LM, 2010. Lapanthus (Bromeliaceae, Bromelioideae): a new genus from the southern Espinhaco Range, Brazil. Systematic Botany 35 (3): 497 - 503, 10.1600/036364410792495908" title="Lapanthus (Bromeliaceae, Bromelioideae): a new genus from the southern Espinhaco Range, Brazil." url="10.1600/036364410792495908" volume="35" year="2010">Louzada and Versieux (2010)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="64">
Besides, some morphological characters such as the rosette shape, the morphology and size of the leaves and the size of the flowers support the decision to include 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Louzada &amp; Wanderley" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="O. B. C. Ribeiro &amp; C. C. Paula" baseAuthorityYear="2012" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Orthophytum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vidaliorum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Orthophytum vidaliorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="R.B.Louzada &amp; L.M.Versieux" authorityYear="2010" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Lapanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Lapanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
