<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="66" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Louzada &amp; Wand." authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="O. B. C. Ribeiro &amp; C. C. Paula" baseAuthorityYear="2012" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Lapanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vidaliorum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Lapanthus vidaliorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in the southernmost part of the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Espinhaço">Espinhaco</normalizedToken>
Range, in an iron-rich region called 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Quadrilátero">Quadrilatero</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ferrífero">Ferrifero</normalizedToken>
(Iron Quadrangle) in the Brazilian state of Minas Gerais. Although it occurs in an iron-rich area, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Louzada &amp; Wand." authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="O. B. C. Ribeiro &amp; C. C. Paula" baseAuthorityYear="2012" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Lapanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vidaliorum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Lapanthus vidaliorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found inhabiting quartizitic-sandstone rocky outcrops (
<bibRefCitation author="Ribeiro, OBC" journalOrPublisher="Brittonia" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" pagination="145 - 148" publicationUrl="10.1007/s12228-009-9105-9" refId="B4" refString="Ribeiro, OBC, Paula, CC, 2010. A new species of Orthophytum (Bromeliaceae, Bromelioideae) from Minas Gerais, Brazil. Brittonia 62 (2): 145 - 148, 10.1007/s12228-009-9105-9" title="A new species of Orthophytum (Bromeliaceae, Bromelioideae) from Minas Gerais, Brazil." url="10.1007/s12228-009-9105-9" volume="62" year="2010">Ribeiro and Paula 2010</bibRefCitation>
) The present combination extends the genus distribution approximately 120 km southward (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Distribution map of Lapanthus vidaliorum (circle), Lapanthus duartei (triangle), and Lapanthus itambensis (square)." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/10175" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
